9. crasqnato Caesare] See Introduction. It happened that the 23d September, Au- gustus’ birth-day, was one of those days in which the early part was ‘nefastus;' that is, the praetor could not hold his court till a later hour than usual. Hence it is marked in the Calendar N. P. (‘ Nefastus Prior '). (See Dict. Ant. p. 186.) So that it was doubly a holiday for Torquatus, and he could lie in bed without damaging his cause, and therefore might sit up late with his friend.
